-- Hong Kong benchmark posts biggest weekly loss in 2 months
-- By Grace Li
-- Fri Jul 11, 2014 04:09AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, July 11 (Reuters) - Hong Kong's benchmark index finished flat on Friday and had its biggest weekly losses in two months, weighed down by underperforming banks and property counters.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> closed little changed at 23,233.45, down 1.3 percent on the week - the largest loss since the week ended May 9. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading offshore Chinese listings in Hong Kong inched up 0.1 percent. It lost slightly more than 1 percent on the week. Leading the losses on the Hang Seng on Friday was China Resources Power <0836.HK>, which sank 3.9 percent, surrendering gains of 3.2 percent on Thursday. Cheung Kong Holdings <0001.HK> slipped 0.6 percent following a 2 percent rise the previous session.